defaultConsistency and comparability
default 
defaulthas emerged as a key common is
defaultsue raised by the PCCs that responded.  
defaultThis is a complex area and there are anomalies caused in part by the system and in part by the nature of statistics.  In the case of the former, for instance, Anti-Social Behaviour incidents 
defaultdo not count as crimes un
defaultder the rules, and the lin
defaulte between ASB, public disorder and low level violence is often blurred
default.  There is also some local flexibility in how rules are applied
default (for instance the time during which a crime must be recorded), which can also cause some anomal
defaulties.   There are a number of caveats that apply to statistics and raw data no matter how accurate it is, such as the need to 
defaultinterpret and triangulat
defaulte 
defaultwith other evidence, before 
defaulti
defaultt can be coherently understood.
default  These issues are explored in more detail be
defaultlow in the context of the questions set out by the PASC.  
